<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB4EF77FF12FF22FE60FF09" blockId="28.[151,469,151,177]" box="[151,469,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading id="0633BB07FFB4EF77FF12FF22FE60FF09" bold="true" box="[151,469,151,177]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FF12FF22FE60FF09" bold="true" box="[151,469,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
3.3. 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FF4EFF22FE60FF09" authority="Rehn, 1950" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[203,469,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">
Dysoniini 
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FECCFF22FE60FF09" author="Rehn, J. A. G." box="[329,469,151,177]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="271 - 319" refId="ref35633" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1950) Studies in the Group Dysoniae (Aphidniae of authors) (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) Part I. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 75 (3 - 4), 271 - 319." type="journal article" year="1950">Rehn, 1950</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB4EF77FF12FF6AFC26FE31" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB4EF77FF12FF6AFC26FE31" blockId="28.[151,1436,223,394]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
The main characteristic of this tribe is the outstanding camouflage, since all species present within this group resemble, in greater or lesser degree, bryophytes and lichens present in humid forests of Neotropical Region, from where 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FF12FE92FEB0FEF9" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[151,261,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Dysoniini">Dysoniini</taxonomicName>
is endemic (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FE14FE92FD19FEF9" author="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J." box="[401,684,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="51 - 60" refId="ref29573" refString="Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. (2011) La tribu Dysoniini parte I: El complejo Dysonia (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae) y su nueva organizacion taxonomica. Journal of Orthoptera Research, 20, 51 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.1665 / 034.020.0105" type="journal article" year="2011">Cadena-Castañeda, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). This tribe comprises 13 genera and 88 species, ten and 30 of them, respectively, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFFB4EF77FE3CFEFEFDB4FEDD" box="[441,513,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. This is the only tribe of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FC92FEFEFC78FEDD" authorityName="BURMEISTER" authorityYear="1838" box="[791,973,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropterinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
previously recorded for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FFB4EF77FA8FFEFEFA2DFEDD" box="[1290,1432,331,357]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, specifically 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB4EF77FE9AFEDAFD26FE32" authority="Rehn, 1950" authorityName="Rehn" authorityYear="1950" box="[287,659,367,394]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Machima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranensis">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FE9AFEDAFDBEFE31" box="[287,523,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Machima paranensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FD97FEDAFD26FE32" author="Rehn, J. A. G." box="[530,659,367,394]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="271 - 319" refId="ref35633" refString="Rehn, J. A. G. (1950) Studies in the Group Dysoniae (Aphidniae of authors) (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) Part I. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 75 (3 - 4), 271 - 319." type="journal article" year="1950">Rehn, 1950</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFFB4EF77FD27FEDAFC32FE31" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[674,903,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB4EF77FC8EFEC5FCF6FE31" box="[779,835,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
